  <title>Introducing OVITO</title>

  <para>
    <informalfigure><screenshot><mediaobject><imageobject>
       <imagedata fileref="images/ovito_screenshot.png" format="PNG" />
    </imageobject></mediaobject></screenshot></informalfigure>

    OVITO is a scientific data visualization and analysis software for working with
    molecular and other particle-based data, typically generated in numeric simulation models from materials science, physics and chemistry disciplines.
    OVITO runs on Windows, Linux, and macOS. It is being developed by <link xlink:href="http://scholar.google.com/citations?user=f8Tw3eEAAAAJ">Dr. Alexander
    Stukowski</link>, who is a research group leader in the materials modeling division at Darmstadt University of Technology, Germany.
  </para>

  <para>
    The first release of OVITO dates back to 2009 and has been described in a paper available
    <link xlink:href="http://stacks.iop.org/0965-0393/18/015012">here</link>. Please cite this paper when
    using OVITO for your research.
  </para>

  <para>
    For further information please visit the official website at <link xlink:href="https://www.ovito.org">www.ovito.org</link>.
  </para>

